Source: La Nacion, San Jose, Costa Rica. Tues 27 Jul 1999
http://www.nacion.co.cr/

Two deaths in Honduras near the El Salvador border due to dengue
----------------------------------
Two people died last month in Honduras due to dengue hemorrhagic fever,
which brings to 3 the number of deaths in this country due to this disease
[dengue hemorrhagic fever, where there have been 30 cases [of dengue
hemorrhagic fever reported since the beginning of the year [1999, an
official of the health sector announced this past Monday.
The director of the Department of Epidemiology of the Ministry of Health,
Antonio Pinel, indicated that the deaths occurred this past June in the
community of Santa Elena, department of La Paz, bordering with El Salvador,
230 km to the west of Tegucigalpa.
According to this official, although the deaths occurred last month, only
now are they able to confirm "that they were due to dengue".
"During June there were 5 cases [of dengue hemorrhagic fever reported
corresponding to a person of 40 years of age and his nephew, 17 years old,
who unfortunately died, and the other 3 [cases were family of theirs, a boy
of 12 years, a girl of 14 and a woman of 30 years" who all recuperated,
specified the official.
Pineda said that the first death due to dengue hemorrhagic presented in
April [1999 and he expressed his surprise at the appearance of cases of
dengue hemorrhagic fever in Santa Elena, "a community at 1850 meters
elevation above sea level, where they believe the vector doesn't live".
[Note there is no mention of possible history of travel to lower altitudes -
MPP
The official announced an investigation and said that the Government has
made efforts, through publicity campaigns, for the population to eliminate
the breeding sites of the mosquitos that transmit dengue. [_Aedes aegypti_
According to official records, in 1998 dengue hemorrhagic fever was
responsible for 7 deaths in Honduras.
....................................jw
